org.apache.sis.metadata.iso.quality

Class DefaultDataQuality

  • Object
    • AbstractMetadata
      • ModifiableMetadata
        • ISOMetadata
          • DefaultDataQuality
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, LenientComparable, IdentifiedObject, DataQuality

    public class DefaultDataQuality
extends ISOMetadata
implements DataQuality
    Quality information for the data specified by a data quality scope.
    Relationship between properties
    According ISO 19115, at least one of lineage and reports shall be provided.
    Since:
    0.3 (derived from geotk-2.1)
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

    Defined in the sis-metadata module (download)

    • Method Detail

      • castOrCopy

        public static DefaultDataQuality castOrCopy(DataQuality object)
        Returns a SIS metadata implementation with the values of the given arbitrary implementation. This method performs the first applicable actions in the following choices:
        • If the given object is null, then this method returns null.
        • Otherwise if the given object is already an instance of DefaultDataQuality, then it is returned unchanged.
        • Otherwise a new DefaultDataQuality instance is created using the copy constructor and returned. Note that this is a shallow copy operation, since the other metadata contained in the given object are not recursively copied.
        Parameters:
        object - The object to get as a SIS implementation, or null if none.
        Returns:
        A SIS implementation containing the values of the given object (may be the given object itself), or null if the argument was null.
